## Schema Tasarimi

### Entity Base Classes
```csharp
public abstract class TenantEntity
{
    public Guid Id { get; protected set; }
    public Guid TenantId { get; protected set; }
}

public abstract class AuditableEntity : TenantEntity
{
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public string CreatedBy { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime? ModifiedAt { get; set; }
    public string? ModifiedBy { get; set; }
    public bool IsDeleted { get; set; }
    public DateTime? DeletedAt { get; set; }
}
```

### Naming Conventions (DB)
- Tables: PascalCase plural (`Orders`, `OrderItems`)
- Columns: PascalCase (`CreatedAt`, `TenantId`)
- Indexes: `IX_{Table}_{Column(s)}` (`IX_Orders_TenantId_Status`)
- Foreign Keys: `FK_{Child}_{Parent}` (`FK_OrderItems_Orders`)
- Unique: `UQ_{Table}_{Column(s)}`
- Check: `CK_{Table}_{Rule}`

## EF Core 9 Configuration

### Fluent API Pattern
```csharp
public class OrderConfiguration : IEntityTypeConfiguration<Order>
{
    public void Configure(EntityTypeBuilder<Order> builder)
    {
        builder.ToTable("Orders");
        builder.HasKey(x => x.Id);
        builder.Property(x => x.TenantId).IsRequired();
        builder.Property(x => x.OrderNumber).HasMaxLength(50).IsRequired();
        builder.Property(x => x.Status).HasConversion<string>().HasMaxLength(30);
        builder.Property(x => x.TotalAmount).HasPrecision(18, 4);
        builder.HasIndex(x => new { x.TenantId, x.Status }).HasDatabaseName("IX_Orders_TenantId_Status");
        builder.HasQueryFilter(x => !x.IsDeleted && x.TenantId == _tenantId);
    }
}
```

### JSON Columns (EF Core 9)
```csharp
builder.OwnsOne(x => x.Metadata, m =>
{
    m.ToJson();
